<inglise> 76/604/EEC: Commission Recommendation of 14 July 1976 to the Member States on the use of straw </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI SOOVITUS liikmesriikidele p&otilde;hu kasutamise kohta 14. juuli 1976 (76/604/EM&Uuml;) </eesti>
<inglise> I </inglise>
<eesti> I </eesti>
<inglise> For several weeks now many regions of the Community have been affected by a serious drought which has greatly reduced the production of fodder. </inglise>
<eesti> Mitme n&auml;dala jooksul on &uuml;henduse paljusid piirkondi m&otilde;jutanud t&otilde;sine p&otilde;ud, mis on tunduvalt v&auml;hendanud s&ouml;&ouml;datootmist. </eesti>
<inglise> As a result, the market is in short supply, fodder prices have risen considerably and certain stock-rearing areas of the Community are having difficulty in obtaining supplies. These difficulties seem likely to increase in the next few months. </inglise>
<eesti> See on p&otilde;hjustanud s&ouml;&ouml;da defitsiiti turul, s&ouml;&ouml;da hinnad on m&auml;rgatavalt t&otilde;usnud ja &uuml;henduse teatavatel karjakasvatuspiirkondadel on tarneraskusi, mis j&auml;rgmiste kuude jooksul suurenevad t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt veelgi. </eesti>
<inglise> II </inglise>
<eesti> II </eesti>
<inglise> In cereal-growing areas, straw is normally burnt or ploughed-in after harvest. </inglise>
<eesti> Teraviljakasvatuspiirkondades p&otilde;hk tavaliselt p&otilde;letatakse v&otilde;i k&uuml;ntakse p&auml;rast koristust mulda. </eesti>
<inglise> This straw can, however, be substituted for fodder in animal feed. </inglise>
<eesti> P&otilde;hku saab siiski kasutada loomas&ouml;&ouml;daks. </eesti>
<inglise> In view of the shortage described above, it appears desirable to feed straw to animals in order to make good the short-fall in fodder production at least in part. </inglise>
<eesti> Eespool nimetatud defitsiiti silmas pidades on soovitatav s&ouml;&ouml;ta p&otilde;hk loomadele, et osaliseltki korvata puuduj&auml;&auml;ki s&ouml;&ouml;datootmises. </eesti>
<inglise> It should, moreover, be noted that the burning of straw could in the prevailing dry conditions cause many outbreaks of fire. </inglise>
<eesti> Peale selle tuleb m&auml;rkida, et p&otilde;hu p&otilde;letamine v&otilde;ib kuiva ilma korral p&otilde;hjustada tulekahjusid. </eesti>
<inglise> III </inglise>
<eesti> III </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission therefore recommends that the Member States take all necessary steps to promote the use of straw as animal feed, in particular by prohibiting the burning or ploughing-in of straw. </inglise>
<eesti> Seet&otilde;ttu soovitab komisjon liikmesriikidel v&otilde;tta k&otilde;ik vajalikud meetmed, et soodustada p&otilde;hu kasutamist loomas&ouml;&ouml;dana ja eelk&otilde;ige keelata p&otilde;hu p&otilde;letamine v&otilde;i muldak&uuml;ndmine. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 14 July 1976. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 14. juuli 1976 </eesti>
<inglise> For the Commission P.J. LARDINOIS Member of the Commission </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni nimel komisjoni liige P. LARDINOIS </eesti>
 